        <body>
            <div hand="Smyth, Ethel">
                <opener>
                    Oct
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    77 l
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear>(still piano!)</unclear>
                    <lb/>
                    Sunday
                    <unclear quantity="3" unit="word"/>
                    <settlement>
                        <lb/>
                        Place de
                        <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                        <lb/>
                        Treppe G III
                    </settlement>
                    <salute>
                        My own Darling
                        <persName key="Struht, Nina Emma" ref="##GND-ID">Mother</persName>
                    </salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    Soo so many thanks for your
                    <lb/>
                    Letter but do you know Mother Darling
                    <lb/>
                    it took me more than 20 minutes to
                    <lb/>
                    read it &
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    1/2 a page is still a
                    <lb/>
                    mystery to me.
                    <hi rend="underline">Do</hi>
                    ask Pap to
                    <lb/>
                    give that horrid cheap blue paper
                    <lb/>
                    to the Children who write
                    <unclear quantity="2" unit="word"/>
                    -
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear quantity="2" unit="word"/>
                    - whose letters are
                    <hi rend="underline">almost</hi>
                    <lb/>
                    readable even when written on that
                    <lb/>
                    paper. But you write large & black
                    <lb/>
                    & it´s
                    <hi rend="underline">utterly</hi>
                    impossible to make
                    <lb/>
                    out 1/2 your letter unless you wrote
                    <lb/>
                    on only one side of the paper. & in
                    <lb/>
                    the
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    that
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    be false economy.
                    <lb/>
                    When aunt
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    wrote to me from
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear>Frimhurst</unclear>
                    – she had to write so - &
                    <lb/>
                    her hand is also very black.
                    <lb/>
                    If you write on blue
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    paper
                    <lb/>
                    I only get such a short letter &
                    <pb/>
                    As one depends a good deal upon letters
                    <lb/>
                    from home surely he could get some
                    <lb/>
                    other paper? You see I am
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    one
                    <lb/>
                    on this subject!! as I have already
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    two
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    appeals to papa!!!
                </p>
                <p>
                    I'm in a great
                    <unclear quantity="3" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    having a return of my Schnupfen!
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear quantity="2" unit="word"/>
                    everyone has one
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    the weather has been horrid. A
                    <lb/>
                    hot
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    & a
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    to which
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    East winds are a
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    ! Then I´ve
                    <lb/>
                    overworked myself a little and
                    <lb/>
                    fear I must continue to do so
                    <lb/>
                    for a day or two till my present
                    <lb/>
                    <persName key="Beethoven, Ludwig van" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/118508288">Beethoven</persName>
                    Concerto & the
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    Sonata are finished. I am
                    <lb/>
                    practising five hours a day at
                    <lb/>
                    least - & till all
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    in
                    <unclear>hand</unclear>
                    are completed it`s hand
                    <lb/>
                    work. Today I shall have
                    <unclear>rather</unclear>
                    <lb/>
                    fun tho. Frau Prof is going to
                    <lb/>
                    chaperone me & 2 friends to one
                    <lb/>
                    of those
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    Concerts one
                    <lb/>
                    can only find on
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    the
                    <lb/>
                    Continent. At which
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <pb/>
                    Husband who looks an awful little
                    <lb/>
                    donkey is going to declaim! (for
                    <lb/>
                    a charity). The 2 friends are the two prettiest girls here. Ony my
                    <lb/>
                    blonde friend Miss
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    . The other a
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    .
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    . The brownest
                    <lb/>
                    brunette you can imagine with
                    <lb/>
                    jet black hair, & eyes like black
                    <lb/>
                    diamonds. I am
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    sure she
                    <lb/>
                    &
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    (who have
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    met
                    <lb/>
                    each other) won't hit it off. Res-
                    <lb/>
                    pect some fun
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    my
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    beauties!
                </p>
                <p>
                    <lb/>
                    The Jubilee Singers have been
                    <lb/>
                    Performing in the Gewandhaus
                    <lb/>
                    & . as you may imagine – as –
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    the Germans not a little.
                    <lb/>
                    . I think one of the Gentlemen
                    <lb/>
                    (primo basso)
                    <hi rend="underline">must</hi>
                    be
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    - with his face dyed!
                    <lb/>
                    Then last night at the Cham-
                    <lb/>
                    ber music (do you remember at
                    <lb/>
                    Aunt Louisa´s that day our
                    <lb/>
                    Discussion about the Chamber pieces!)
                    <pb/>
                    <persName key="Saint-Saens, Camille" ref="https://d-nb.info/gnd/11875081X">Saint-Saens</persName>
                    Saint-Saens the great French composer
                    <lb/>
                    - who besides that is the greatest
                    <lb/>
                    player I ever heard bar Rubinstein
                    <lb/>
                    (Tho' probably he is not so many
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    Of one
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    as well) played - &
                    <lb/>
                    was called back 9 times
                    <unclear>. +</unclear>
                    played
                    <lb/>
                    2 Encores!! At the
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    of all
                    <lb/>
                    Things for the benefit of the Conserva-
                    <lb/>
                    Tories who went utterly
                    <hi rend="underline">wild</hi>
                    over
                    <lb/>
                    Him & (when he was here a month
                    <lb/>
                    ago) sent him a testimonial!! When
                    <lb/>
                    Saint-Saens drove away such a
                    <unclear quantity="1" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    You never heard. The wanted to
                    <lb/>
                    take the horses out - & drag him
                    <lb/>
                    home – luckily for him however
                    <lb/>
                    (as he was undoubtedly hungry)
                    <lb/>
                    His coachman drove on at the
                    <lb/>
                    first cry of "Spanne die Pferde
                    <lb/>
                    Ab!!". (While I have been sitting
                    <lb/>
                    Writing this letter at my window
                    <lb/>
                    Which looks out on the Promenade
                    <lb/>
                    Abt. 100 yards away I've seen
                    <lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">3</hi>
                    dwarfs go by!!! This will give
                    <lb/>
                    You an idea of the number in
                    <lb/>
                    Germany – Its
                    <hi rend="underline">horrid</hi>
                    .
                </p>
                <closer>
                    Well Mother
                    <lb/>
                    Darling – I´ve written 3 sheets of
                    <unclear quantity="2" unit="word"/>
                    <lb/>
                    Susan &
                    <hi rend="underline">must</hi>
                    shut up. Dear
                    <lb/>
                    Love to all. Alas for Philis who
                    <lb/>
                    Won´t be my only joy any more now. But
                    <lb/>
                    Of course she must be used somehow.
                    <lb/>
                    Yours ever devoted
                    <unclear quantity="2" unit="word"/>
                </closer>
                <!--
                    
